I'd never really known how to explain my past abusive relationship with my ex, but of all the posts I've seen, this one comes pretty close. Criticizing the things and people you love while making it seem that you're lucky to have them because they """"like something about you that other people wouldn't."""" I remember one time he told me in anger """"The only thing I find attractive about you is your body."""" That relationship ended around 2.5 years ago but I'm still dealing with some of the self-confidence issues that were strengthened or created during that relationship.
